    <h1>The Elements of Style</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">William Strunk Jr. &middot; 1918 &middot; <a href="https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/37134">Read the original (Project Gutenberg, public domain)</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Forty-three pages. That's it. Strunk wrote the shortest useful specification for English prose. Rule 17: "Omit needless words." He practiced what he preached&mdash;the rule is three words. The book is a checklist: it tells you what's wrong, not what to write. Apply it, and your prose clears up. Ignore it, and nobody will tell you why they stopped reading.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: type-checker pipeline -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-8">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 520 200" class="w-full max-w-lg" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
